title: Haworthia Emelyae
description: This species is one of the "retuse" species of Haworthia, meaning that it usually grows sunken beneath the ground with its flattened leaves only showing on the surface.

title: Haworthiopsis Tulista Pumila
description: It is an evergreen, winter-growing succulent plant with sharp succulent leaves arranged in rosettes of 20 cm in diameter.

title: Haworthia Retusa Renny Unknown
description: It's an unnamed Renny seedling with some retusa in it. It glows when the sun hits it.

title: Haworthia Truncata ex Sakai
description: In the wild, plants are often half-buried, leaving only the tips of the leaves visible above the soil.

title: Haworthia Atrofusca Watermelon
description: It grows in areas of summer rainfall and winter drought, in rocky soils at elevation where water drains sharply.

title: Haworthia Maughanii Variegated
description: Maughanii likes a warm, dry and sunny environment, not cold, afraid of high temperature and strong light, and tolerant to semi-shade. It is also known as the elephantfoot grass.

title: Haworthia Pumila Donuts
description: The plant rarely offsets, so most propagation is by seed, though leaf cuttings can also be rooted when larger leaves are used.

title: Haworthia Tourmaline Rivers
description: This is one of a cultivar group created by John Chwekun who hybridizes and cultivates genetically unique succulents using slow, natural processes.
